If you worked in more than one state, you may be able to combine the wages you earned during your base period into a combined wage claim. Combining these wages could increase your maximum and/or your weekly benefit amount. If you did not tell the EDD at the time you filed your claim that you worked in more than one state, call the EDD immediately. See the inside cover of this handbook for instructions. If you believe the earnings shown are incorrect or are not your wages, contact the EDD IMMEDIATELY and request a correction. If you give false information or withhold facts to receive benefits you may be subject to disqualification and criminal penalties.
